snippet.textDisplay: Saying to all Indian listeners and also  from other countries, appreciating CSP superb performances. Very well written thoughts by you for us all good people in India, Pakistan and the world. I have lived out of Pakistan since age 21 and my grown sons here in the US have very good and decent friends from school age of Indian descent. My oldest son keeps on saying that even being Kashmiri Muslims our ancestor must have converted from Hinduism.  Anyhow, we are the same people and must be together and appreciate each other and remove the British practice of "Divide and Conquer". Please read the book, "Observations, Perceptions & Questions".
